# Routine: correctness

## Purpose

To ensure the Skaia project remains consistent, up-to-date, and free of inefficiencies or documentation drift by regularly scanning for actionable issues and enforcing alignment between code, docs, and specs.

## Responsibilities

- Periodically scan the Skaia project for inconsistencies, outdated documentation, orphaned files, or inefficient practices
- Focus on README and spec files, but also check code, migrations, and project structure for alignment with documentation
- Always find at least one actionable criticism per run

## Goal

Prove the routine's value by always surfacing at least one actionable issue, even if minor, and drive continuous improvement.

## Principles

- Every run must surface at least one actionable issue
- Documentation and code must always be in sync
- Prioritize clarity, maintainability, and alignment with best practices
- Communicate and document all findings and suggestions

## Workflow

1. Scan all README.md, .spec, .specs, and .spec.md files
2. Check backend/internal/migrations/, backend/internal/utils/, backend/models/ for alignment with docs/specs
3. Identify inconsistencies, outdated docs, orphaned files, or inefficient practices
4. Document at least one actionable criticism per run
5. Suggest improvements and prioritize them
6. Communicate findings and update onboarding/developer docs as needed

### Pseudocode

```
for doc in (README.md, .spec*, .specs*):
   check alignment with code/migrations/models
   find at least one actionable issue
   document criticism, suggestion, priority, next steps
update onboarding/dev docs if needed
```

## Contexts

- All README.md files
- All .spec, .specs, and .spec.md files in the project
- backend/internal/migrations/
- backend/internal/utils/
- backend/models/

